One recommended way to verify errors in your program before release, be it by invaled parameters being passed, unexpected values being changed, or anything else it is a good Idea to use ***Assertions***. They are made so we can catch errors and fix them before release working code.

One way to use them are setting a **precondition**: a condition that must be true pior to code execution:
```cpp
void printDivision(int x, int y){
	if (y == 0){
		std::cerr << "Error: Could not divide by zero\n";
		return;
	}
	std::cout << static_cast<double>(x) / y;
}
```
